clouds.py<pre><code>import os
import yaml

clouds = {
  "clouds":{
    "openstack": {
      "auth" : {
        "auth_url" : os.environ["OS_AUTH_URL"],
        "project_name": os.environ["OS_PROJECT_NAME"],
        "project_domain_name": os.environ["OS_PROJECT_DOMAIN_NAME"],
        "username": os.environ["OS_USERNAME"],
        "user_domain_name": os.environ["OS_USER_DOMAIN_NAME"],
        "password": os.environ["OS_PASSWORD"],
      },
      "region_name": os.environ["OS_REGION_NAME"],
      "identity_api_version":  os.environ["OS_IDENTITY_API_VERSION"],
      "interface": "public"
    }
  }
}

print(yaml.dump(clouds))
</code></pre> <p>First you need to source your <code>openrc</code> file so that the <code>OS_</code> variables are available.</p> <pre><code>source PROJECT-openrc.sh
</code></pre> <p>Now you can execute the Python script and a <code>clouds.yaml</code> will be written.</p> <pre><code>python3 clouds.py &gt; clouds.yaml
</code></pre>

